sentences: Natalia Noemi "Teddy" Sinclair (née Cappuccini; born 15 August 1986), is an English singer, songwriter and actress.
She is currently the lead vocalist of the band Cruel Youth, which also releases music under the name The Powder Room.
As Natalia Kills, Sinclair released the studio albums Perfectionist (2011) and Trouble (2013).
As Natalia Kills, Sinclair released the studio albums Perfectionist (2011) and Trouble (2013).
In 2014, she married fellow singer Willy Moon.
Since July 2015, Sinclair has gone by and performed under her legal name Teddy Sinclair.
In 2016, she started her own band, Cruel Youth, with whom she has released the EP, +30mg (2016).
In 2016, she started her own band, Cruel Youth, with whom she has released the EP, +30mg (2016).
Her biggest commercial singles were the BVMI gold-certified singles "Mirrors" (2010), "Free" with Will.i.am, and the UK-top 40 hit, "Champagne Showers" with American pop duo LMFAO.
She received a Grammy Award nomination in 2017 for co-writing Rihanna's single "Kiss It Better".
In March 2015, Sinclair and her husband, Willy Moon, were fired as judges from New Zealand X Factor for their harsh comments towards one of the contestants.
